post_text: "The District does not condone the insensitive tweets posted by a volunteer coach, who has been notified that he will no longer be associated with the Williamsville South football team. We will never forget the tragic loss of lives this country suffered on September 11, 2001."

post_text:
REMINDER: In accordance with Executive Order 202.39, the District Vote is being extended to June 16, 2020, with the following provisions:

- Absentee ballots can be received by the District Clerk through the mail until 5 p.m. on June 16, 2020.

- Absentee ballots that are dropped off/hand-delivered will be accepted by the District Clerk until 5 p.m. on June 9, 2020.

- Absentee ballots will not be able to be hand-delivered/dropped off to the District Clerk after 5 p.m. on June 9, 2020. Additionally, any dropbox used for hand delivery will be closed and removed at 5 p.m. on June 9, 2020.

FULL DETAILS: https://www.williamsvillek12.org/alert_detail.php

Williamsville CSD is proud to introduce our three School Resource Officers who will be servicing our schools! Amherst Police Department

They will have offices at the three high schools and service the “feeder pattern” communities of each of those schools.

Andrew Heim- North High, Casey Middle, Heim Middle, Heim Elementary, Dodge Elementary

Andrew Edwards- East High, Transit Middle, Maple East Elementary, Country Parkway Elementary

James Persons- South High, Mill Middle, Forest Elementary, Maple West Elementary

post_text:
Mill Middle hosts their 1st PIE IT FORWARD! Check out the full story today on News 4 WIVB Buffalo at 4:45🥧🥧

Mill Middle students in Mrs. Pecori's FACS classes used Mrs. Tuskes' special family recipes to make homemade pies as part of their Pie It Forward project. As a result, these classes will donate more than 50 fresh pies to the Buffalo City Mission for Thanksgiving this year!

The students worked together and learned to:
✅Make dough from scratch
✅Cut & Season Apples🍎
✅Make pumpkin filling🎃
✅Make crumb topping
✅And even create lattice top by hand👩‍🍳

Congratulations Mill Middle on such an incredible program and thank you for all that you have done this holiday season!

#MillGivesBack🐎🐎

Friday, Williamsville East High students came together & donated over 4,300 cans of food as part of their annual Turkey Basket Project. This breaks last year's record and will feed over 500 local families this Thanksgiving! #EastGivesBack

Mrs. Mahaney's Youth Leadership classes spearheaded the fundraising by making promotional posters and making sure the entire school got involved!

The Williamsville East Student Council also donates 100 frozen turkeys to local families for Thanksgiving.

See the full story on WGRZ - Channel 2, Buffalo this Wednesday

Yesterday, we had 9 student-athletes from across the District who signed their National Letters of Intent, committing to colleges across the country to further their education and continue their athletic careers. Congratulations to all of them! We look forward to following their future academic and athletic achievements!

North High School:
Lianna Van Sice - Soccer - Youngstown State U.
Gabrielle Ciambella - Soccer - Roberts Wesleyan College

East High School:
Joe Amici - Lacrosse- Northern Greenville U.
Gretchen Beyer - Soccer - Daemen College
Lyla Militello - Lacrosse - U. of Akron
Anna Miller - Soccer - Loyola U. Maryland
Mia Wendell - Ice Hockey - Yale

South High School:
Elizabeth Fox - Softball - Seton Hill U.
Owen Birkman - Baseball - SUNY at Albany
